By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Senator representing Enugu east senatorial district, Senator Chimaroke Nnamani has reacted to news of his expulsion by the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), saying he will soon make revelations that will shock Nigerians. Sundiata Post recalls that the National Working Committee of the PDP on Friday (today), expelled Chimaraoke and 7 other chieftains of the party, over alleged anti-party activities including other weighty offences that infringe on the party’s constitution. The expulsion of Senator Chimaroke Nnamani was contained in a statement by the National Publicity Secretary of the party, Debo Ologunagba in Abuja. Ologunagba stated “The NWC of the PDP at its 566th meeting today, Friday, February 10, 2023, approved the expulsion of the following individuals from the Party for anti-Party activities”. But in a report by THE PUNCH, the former governor of Enugu state when asked about his position on his expulsion by the party said “I will make a release soon”. Senator Nnamani is the PDP candidate in the 2023 general election for Enugu East Senatorial Zone.